getNewDialog

public DialogActivity getNewDialog(DialogActivity incomingDialog,
                                   boolean useSameCallId)
                            throws javax.sip.SipException
Description copied from interface: SleeSipProvider
This method creates a new SIP Dialog, starts a new Activity in the SLEE, and returns the new DialogActivity. The new Dialog is a UAC Dialog. This method copies the local and remote addresses from incoming Dialog to the newly created Dialog. It generates a new local tag and the remote tag will be null. If the useSameCallId parameter is true then the newly created Dialog will use the Call ID from the incoming Dialog, otherwise a new Call ID is generated. This method takes the following arguments First request sent via this activity MUST be dialog creating request.

useSameCallId - - if call-id should be reused

acceptCancel

public boolean acceptCancel(CancelRequestEvent cancelEvent,
                            boolean isProxy)
Description copied from interface: SleeSipProvider
This method is a convenience method for handling CANCEL requests. When a CANCEL arrives, and application can ask the RA to handle the request by calling this method. The behavior of the RA is dependent on whether the CANCEL matched the INVITE, and also whether the application is acting as a proxy or not, as determined by the isProxy parameter. The method returns true if the CANCEL matched an INVITE. The behavior of the method is summarized as follows.
isProxy==false isProxy==true
CANCEL matched INVITE Send ÔøΩ200 OKÔøΩ response to CANCEL. Send ÔøΩ487 Request TerminatedÔøΩ response to INVITE. Send ÔøΩ200 OKÔøΩ response to CANCEL. The Proxy application must cancel outstanding branches and wait for responses (RFC3261 ÔøΩ16.10).
CANCEL did not match INVITE Send ÔøΩ481 Call or Transaction Does Not ExistÔøΩ response to CANCEL. Do nothing. Proxy application must statelessly forward the CANCEL downstream (RFC3261 ÔøΩ16.10).
The resource adaptor is expected to check if the CANCEL request was processed by any SBBs. If the CANCEL request was not processed by an SBB, the RA is expected to send a ÔøΩ481 Call or Transaction Does Not ExistÔøΩ.

Specified by:
acceptCancel in interface SleeSipProvider
Returns:

forwardForkedResponse

public DialogActivity forwardForkedResponse(javax.sip.ServerTransaction origServerTransaction,
                                            javax.sip.message.Response response)
                                     throws javax.sip.SipException
Description copied from interface: SleeSipProvider
This method is used when forwarding a forked response, that was received in a DialogForkedEvent. A transparent B2BUA application must use this method to forward forked responses upstream. This method sends the response on the supplied javax.sip.ServerTransaction, and creates a new Dialog Activity that the SBB should attach to, to receive mid-dialog requests on the new dialog. Sending a forked response upstream using the sendResponse(javax.sip.message.Response) method on javax.sip.ServerTransaction will not work correctly, because if the caller sends any mid-dialog requests on the new dialog, the RA Entity will not match them with a dialog activity, and will not fire these request events on the Dialog Activity. If the response is a final response, all other early dialogs will be terminated.

Specified by:
forwardForkedResponse in interface SleeSipProvider
Returns:
Throws:
javax.sip.SipException
